      • getNRectangles

        private int[][] getNRectangles(int NCount)
                        throws java.io.IOException
        ***Must call calculateCLBDensity before calling getNRectangles*** Calls the list rectangles algorithm N times to find the N largest free rectangles. Each iteration fills in the previous iteration's rectangles so they are no longer considered free area.
        Parameters:
        NCount - How many of the largest free rectangles of CLBs in the design to report
        Returns:
        A 2D array NCount x 4 in size that represents the N largest rectangles in this format: [x, y, width, height]
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
                 throws java.io.IOException
        This function will be setup to be best used in TCL within Vivado. Passing an edif and xpn will provide several metrics to give a rough idea of "debuggability." Metrics include: Resource usage counts Density of tile usage (plotted with python after calling MetricAnalyzer) A N-count long list of the N largest open rectangles of tiles in the design
        Parameters:
        args - Must include the EDIF, XPN of a design and a data path to place data. May include 'N' to indicate how many of the largest free rectangles of free tiles should be provided.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - FileWriter requires this exception.
